30/06/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Public Order Minister George Voulgarakis met with Interpol Secretary General Ronald Noble in Athens on Tuesday (29 June). Greek Police Chief Fotis Nassiakos also participated. They discussed security preparations for the Olympics, which begin on 13 August. Voulgarakis said that at this time there is no information from any intelligence agency in the world about any threat to the Games. (ANA, MPA - 29/06/04)
